cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SE 

This paper discusses the ethical implications of machine learning algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. However, the focus on error analysis and the evaluation of machine learning models makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) the most likely category. The discussion of discriminatory-aware machine learning algorithms also suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a likely category. The ethical implications of avoiding error analysis could also fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the mention of non-interpretable machine learning algorithms such as deep learning suggests cs.SE (Software Engineering) as a possible category.
